        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Low levels (4-50):<BR>+ could solo<BR>+ killing white/yellow/reds with fear<BR>+ group efficency (through snare/fearing) was a big plus<BR>+ variety of spells (root, fear, snare, feign death, pets, charm, dots, and lifetaps)</P><P>Higher levels (49+) (lower stuff still applicable):<BR>+ variety of strategies<BR>+ infinite mana while doing damage (splurt/bond of death/lich)</P><P>Highest levels (55+) (lower stuff still applicable):<BR>+ death peace<BR>+ monk pet and  spectre pet<BR>+/- pyre, great spell but can't afford it<BR>+ zevfeer, ups our group usefulness<BR>+ paralyzing earth (cause of resistance changes lasts near 3 min almost guarenteed)<BR>- the fact most guilds put us at the bottom of the usefulness scale<BR>- our reign of kings of dots will be challenged in PoP<BR>- unsnareable monsters<BR>- unfearable monsters<BR>- summoning monsters<BR>- highly immune no loot monsters<BR>- 55/59 class aaexp abilities.  Many of the 55 abilities aren't applicable to necros, and our selection of 59 abilities are duds.</P><P>At low levels I felt rewarded.  A new spell rank increased power dramatically, killing a red 5 levels above you gave a sizable exp boost.  At higher levels I'm viewing the game much more as a time sink with fewer rewards.</P><P> </font></td>
