 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>nizzamne</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> 1- Independence. Necros dont rely on anyone.. I dont have to beg for KEI to be efficient when i solo, i dont need anyone, because im self-sufficient. Of course i need ports, thats the only thing that comes in my mind about the independence part. I pay 20pp for it and thats it.</P><P>2- Liberty. As a necro, i couldnt care less about faction! Druids, paladins, rangers.. name it, i kill it. I can kill just about everything and dont care because they already hate me (its even more simple with luclin.. shadowheaven/bazaar areas) i could be kos in Paineel (my hometown) and it wouldnt change a thing in my gaming aspect.</P><P>3- Solo. Of course.. i prefer soloing than grouping, thats why i made a necro. Maybe its just me but when im in a group (on my ranger or shaman alt) when theres a wipeout or a bad pull, im in the group. I know that its not everyone that has the same "techniques" of gameplay and we play our chars like the way we are used to.. but i dont want to die because of other's errors.. when i solo with my necro, if i die its usually my fault or an "exterior" element (a.k.a. bad resists run, wanderer in my spot, druid rooting my feared mob to "help" and poofing my pet because of that etc.)</P><P>4- Bragging Rights. Yup, im a fucking showoff! I solo in Akheva at 51 and make excellent xp.. i see all the time levels 60 druids, rangers wizards.. doing their AA there.. but me, im the "little 51" that does xp in a zone where im not supposed to be (in da teeth). At 50 i soloed the Corrupted Seafury Cyclops, hes 51-52 and yes he summons. I did the allilewsaur at 51 (tons of hps and hits in the mid to high hundreds). Where mages and wizards go and run oom, im successfull and damn proud of it.</P><P>5- Other misc stuff. The look (erud with a scythe = sheckzy), The titles (heretic, defiler and warlock) we are the only pure caster class that gets a custom Class title (we get Lich others get Sage) the fact that i can make money very easily (necros are excellent farmers) the fact that i level faster than most classes.. the fact that.. the fact that i like to play a necro.</P><P>My 2cp and beyond</P><P>Nizz</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Falstep</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Ok, my best friend’s roommate was a beta tester for EQ.  He’s the one that put “EQ” in my vocabulary.  Because of him I read all about it before it came out.  I got the game on the second day of the US release and anxiously sat around hours downloading patches.</P><P>I had it all figured out.  I was going to create this DESK.  I had a name and family history all made up for him.  I was beside myself with anticipation.</P><P>Finally the game booted up and I logged onto the Solusek Ro server (picked at random).  Then I created….whatever his name was, the DESK.  I figured out how to talk and shout.  Then I started running around looking for my guild.  I ran and ran and ran.  On my old PC, Neriak was very dark and I could not adjust it.  Then I gave up on finding my guild and just started looking for a way out of the city.  Then, about to vomit from motion sickness, I had to log off.</P><P>It was very disheartening.  I tried again to get him out, but started getting sick again.  I then decided to give up on him.  I went through and made a bunch of characters, finally liking my Troll warrior, Roazenkranz (Roazy to his friends).  I played him until some of my friends and I decided to try the new team PvP servers that were opening.  We had a great time until all the goodie teams (we were shorties) started setting up truces and cooperating…/spit.  I wanted to go evil, but others didn’t (freaks).  About this time Tribunal opened and we decided to go there (we all lagged very badly on SolRo for some reason.  I still do).</P><P>My RL best friend, meanwhile, had played a necro up to 20th or so and kept raving about how much fun it was.  The last piece of the puzzle was a mistake on my part.  I was talking to a friend and meant to say, “One false move and the blonde gets it!”  Instead, I said, “One false step and the blonde gets it.”  Later I kept saying “False Step” over and over.  I liked the way it sounded and the idea of it…a false step, a deceitful move.  Eventually, I decided to make a character named False Step.  It didn’t take long to decide that False Step should be a necromancer, just based on the name and my thoughts behind it.</P><P>Much to my disappointment False was taken (belongs to some some double secret ninja uber shaman I think), so I sat and thought for a second and just sort of shoved the two words together…Falstep.  I started playing him and, even though I have started countless alts, he is by far my favorite character.</P><P>It was, of course, the class that kept me playing him.  I very much enjoy the Necromancer.  What I enjoy most is the freedom of it.  I have needed a group, which is good for me because I have a very low tolerance for idiots.  Nowadays I group with friends and guildies almost exclusively, so it’s very nice to know I can kill just about anything I can stick darkness on.</P><P>But also, I love the cycle of death game.  Leech off my HPs for mana, suck HPs off the mobs…keeping that balance going.  I dig it.</P><P>And CRs...I don't group with strangers a lot, but I'll try to get anyone's corpse for them.  I have gotten pretty talented at getting corpses.  Several times I have had whole groups sitting at a zone or on a zone wall while I went and got their corpses one at a time, because they kept dying trying to get them.  Falstep's Corpse Retrieval Service.  I like it.</P><P>In closing, let me say that I am not saying that Necro’s are perfect.  It works well for me because of my style of play, but that does not mean that others should be forced into my style of play by Verant.  And that’s not to mention the spell drops being messed up…</P><P>-Falstep</P><P><BR> </font></td>
