 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Delsharin</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I love the independence of the necromancer, the pet, the awesome spell names (what other class can compete with spells like Zevfeer's Theft of Vitae and Gangrenous Touch of Zum'uul?), and the surprisingly versatility of the class.  Many times I am frustrated because I can't get in a group but there have been other times when I've been the only thing making a group possible.  When I was in my mid-20s in the Lake of Ill Omen I saved my party's rear countless times when we pulled multiple Sarnaks, because I simply mezzed the snot out of the adds with Screaming Terror.  I saved other casters and clerics with that numerous times.  More recently (I'm 38) I've done the same in Dawnshroud, and there was one time I was grouped with a monk and warrior after our cleric left and I ended up not only keeping them healed (the monk's Mend was nice, of course), but mezzing adds and doing damage through lifetap DoTs and nukes and since I was in Call of Bones the entire time I did it all with very little net mana usage, allowing us to pull near-continuously.  That was a real rush because I can't think of any other class that can do all of that so well.  I know it was under very specific conditions but it still made me proud to be a necromancer.</P><P>It's also been a rush to take down red /con hill giants (which nonetheless gave crappy XP- silly giants) and to destroy a white griffin with painful ease.  </P><P>I will admit that I have issues being wanted by other people, groups, and guilds and I'm sensitive about insults to my class for being useless, and it's a lonely existence since I've really started soloing full-time- basically I've gone from 34 to (soon) 39 soloing almost exclusively (as opposed to 24 to 34, when I grouped a lot) and it's been kind of sad because it's less exciting than grouping.  None the less, soloing is cool because you can rely only on yourself and you can go wherever and do whatever you want, whenever you want.</P><P>Oh, and the fact that I might eventually (yeah, keep dreaming) get a mana regen spell that blows the much-vaunted KEI out of the water makes me very happy. :)</P><P> </font></td>
