 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Shaymizz</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Well, I originally started with an ogre warrior, because I like to play combinations that don't see a lot of use.  And then I got online and saw I wasn't really a minority.<BR>But at least I thought warriors would kick butt and take names.<BR>And he did, until about 20th level or so.  20th-40th it was harder to get xp without grouping.  And 40+, damn near impossible.  At 50th, I went to fight a hill giant to get cash.  Lost, barely, but lost.  To a mob 15 levels lower than I was.  And if I had won the battle, down time would have taken me 40 minutes to heal back up to full.</P><P>So I started up a necro cause I heard/seen what they could do.</P><P>With my necro, I was soloing HGs at 35.</P><P>Currently, at 46th, I'm soloing stuff that would drop my warrior in under 45 seconds.  Fight time lasts 2 to 3 minutes, but down time is less then 7 minutes.</P><P>Now I don't have to rely on groups to play.  I can play whenever I want.  I can accumulate cash to purchase most whatever I want.  Of course, the battles are entirely repetitive: send in pet, darkness, fear, debuff, dot, re-fear and re-dark and re-dot as necessary.</P><P> </font></td>
