        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I know I already put in a long post, but krule reminded me of something else.  I'll keep it short.  What he said about others necros is true.  I have had absolutely nothing but good experiences with other necros.  Never a camp dispute, a KSing, nothing bad at all.</P><P>Example:</P><P>I hit 49th and had not one of my research words, and had been unable to find the spells for sale.  I log on one day next to the EJ zone in TT.  Sitting there is a 51st necro with his pet up.  I ask him if that's the 49th pet.  He says yes.  I ask if I can gaze at it longingly.  He laughs and says yes.  He then asks if I have any of my 49th research spells, and I say no.  He then hands my BoD and Lich.  I offered money and he refused.</P><P>About an hour later a Warlock buddy of mine logged on.  He had the words for the 49th pet.  He combined them for me and met me in Nexus to hand the spell off to me.</P><P>That pretty much says it all.</P><P><BR>-Falstep</P><P> </font></td>
